So the short answer is that the load files are not completed yet. One machine alone had over 800,000 emails. The 
limitation of the load files is that they can only be generated with 25,000 entries at a time. So I got out as quickly 
as I could what fit that bill. Now along has come all the stuff from the Island that had an expiration date, so that 
took priority. I can now go back and try to generate the stuff that has yet to be processed into load files, but the 
process is slow and painful. Just as an FYI, all the content is available for taint review in FTK right now. 
Senior Forensic Examiner
